Disease scare on Turkey's border
--------------------------------
The article reports massive spread of lumpy skin disease [LSD] in cattle in the Turkish provinces bordering Syria, causing serious economic losses predominantly in Osmaniye, Adana and Kahramanmaras. The disease is being repeatedly introduced with infected cattle from Syria crossing the "porous", "leaking" border and is locally spread by flies. The vaccine applied by the Ministry of Food, Agriculture and Livestock is said to be a sheep and goat pox vaccine. The disease does not affect human health. Meat prices have risen.

--
